2.02	Syllables	Syllable	A syllable is a unit of organization for a sequence of speech sounds. For example, the word water is composed of two syllables: wa and ter. A syllable is typically made up of a syllable nucleus (most often a vowel) with optional initial and final margins (typically, consonants).	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0f/Syllable.svg/220px-Syllable.svg.png
